# 🌐 1️⃣ API Design Principles

## Simple Idea

A good API should be:

✅ Easy to understand
✅ Consistent
✅ Predictable

---

### Bad API ❌

```text
/getAllUsersDataNow
```

Confusing.

---

### Good API ✅

```text
GET /users
```

Simple and clear.

---

### Mental Model 🧠

Think of road signs.

Good road signs are:

* clear
* consistent
* easy to follow

APIs should be the same.

---

### Golden Rule

Use nouns for resources:

```text
/users
/products
/orders
```

Not actions.

---

### Why It Matters

Good APIs:

* easier to maintain
* easier for teams to use
* fewer bugs

